<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-615-113  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 615 113.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Nov 12 1990 v36 n1835 p25(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>20MB floppies could stymie 4MB market; smaller capacity waits forendorsement. (Spotlight on Disk andamp; Tape Drives special section)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Deagon, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The market for 4Mbyte floppy disk drives has been hindered by thepotential 20Mbyte floppy disk drive technology and by lack ofendorsement from a large manufacturer, such as IBM, Apple orCompaq.andP;  The technology was developed by Toshiba Corp, and severalJapanese manufacturers are ready to ship devices in volume onshort notice.andP;  Analysts claim the 4Mbyte technology will only besuccessful if IBM decides to use it; 4Mbyte floppies have beenendorsed by Next Inc, but Apple and Compaq are not expected toadopt the format.andP;  The 20Mbyte format costs an average of $15 permegabyte, compared to $50 per megabyte for the 4Mbyte format.andO;Firms supporting 4Mbyte floppies include Teac, Mitsubishi, Sony,Chinon and Epson; firms supporting 20Mbyte floppies include BrierTechnology, Insite Peripherals and Springer Technologies Inc.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Disk DrivesStandardsStorage CapacityMarket AnalysisIndustry AnalysisOutlookForecastingFloppy disks.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Worldwide factory revenue forecast, flexible disk drives: 1989-94.andO;(graph)Worldwide sales forecast, flexible disk drives: 1989-94. (graph)Worldwide sales forecast, 3.5-inch FDDs: 1989-94. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>